<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
	<title>CSS Toggle Switches with Foundation</title>
	<meta name="description" content="Accessible, screen-reader friendly, CSS-only toggle switches with full keyboard access and mobile support, using standard form controls.">
	<meta name="author" content="Ionuț Colceriu">

	<link rel="stylesheet" href="bower_components/normalize-css/normalize.css">

	<!-- Docs styles, not required by the switches -->
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="dist/docs/docs.css">

	<!-- Foundation styles -->
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="dist/docs/foundation.css">

	<!-- Prism Syntax Highlighter -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bower_components/prism/prism.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bower_components/prism/prism-okaidia.css">
    <script src="bower_components/prism/prism.js"></script>
</head>
<body>

	<div class="container-foundation">

		<a class="ribbon" href="https://github.com/ghinda/css-toggle-switch" target="_blank">
			<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_darkblue_121621.png" alt="Fork me on GitHub">
		</a>

		<header class="row">
			<h1>CSS Toggle Switches</h1>

			<p class="description">Accessible, CSS-only toggle switches with full keyboard access and mobile support, using standard form controls. </p>

			<p class="frameworks">
				These examples use Foundation, you can also use the <a href="index.html">switches alone</a>,
				or with <a href="bootstrap.html">Bootstrap</a>.
			</p>

			<div class="small-2 header-toggle">
				<div class="switch">
					<input id="x" name="switch-x" type="radio" checked>
					<label for="x" onclick="">Off</label>

					<input id="x1" name="switch-x" type="radio">
					<label for="x1" onclick="">On</label>

					<span></span>
				</div>
			</div>

		</header>

		<div data-alert class="alert-box secondary">
			Foundation 4 now includes it's own <a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/docs/components/switch.html">switch component</a>, based on this one, that allows you to switch between two options.

			<br><br>

			If you need to choose between more than two options, I recommend you use <a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/docs/components/button-groups.html">button groups</a> or radio buttons.
		</div>

		<footer>

			<hr>

			<h3>
				<a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/" target="_blank">Get Foundation.</a>
			</h3>

			<a href="https://github.com/ghinda/css-toggle-switch">CSS Toggle Switches</a> by <a href="http://ghinda.net">Ionuț Colceriu</a>.
		</footer>

	</div>

